						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa,</hi> Tiruvālanduṟai-uḍaiyār temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 8: 979 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that an individual Sāvāṉ Tiruvāṉdattaṉ gave four <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land out of a7laichchey at Śrīkaṇṭa-maṅgalam for burning a perpetual lamp, with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of oil daily, to the god Mahādēva of Tiruvālanduṟai in Puḷḷamaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Kiḻāṟ-kūṟṟam.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Varalāṟu</hi> Vol. III, p. 22.</p>						

						</summary>
